<paragraph blockId="31.[192,600,771,827]" box="[192,480,803,827]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
(
<figureCitation box="[201,308,803,827]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="199.[192,281,1807,1828]" captionTargetBox="[264,1312,195,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-13@199.[261,1344,192,1775]" captionTargetPageId="199" captionText="PLATE 3. A-I. Dorsal habitus. (A) Hiatusorus aviformis, sp. nov.; (B) Hiatusorus supraspinosus, sp. nov.; (C) Hiatusorus robustus, sp. nov.; (D) Laosolidia tuberis, sp. nov.; (E) Laosolidia complexa, sp. nov.; (F) Laosolidia longiserrata, sp. nov.; (G) Olidiana egregia (Schumacher) (male); (H) (Olidiana egregia (Schumacher) (female); (I) Olidiana tuberis, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181726/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Plate 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[320,472,803,827]" captionStart="Figures 141-147" captionStartId="152.[192,287,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[275,1334,212,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-18@152.[263,1348,192,1701]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figures 141-147. Genitalia, Hiatusorus aviformis, sp. nov. 141) Male pygofer, lateral view. 142) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view. 143) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view. 144) Style, lateral view. 145) Style, dorsal view. 146) Connective, caudal view. 147) Subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181630/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 141-147</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[192,1441,867,1403]" box="[192,882,867,891]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,476,867,891]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Description. Length.</emphasis>
Male 8.80 mm., female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[192,1441,867,1403]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,536,899,923]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">External morphology.</emphasis>
Large, robust species. General color light to dark brown to black; forewings brown, large black triangulate mark at apex of clavus, transparent area distally, apical 1/5 dark brown, veins interspersed with short yellow and black stripes, cells translucent except at apex, mesonotum black, apex yellow; pronotum black, bullae dark yellow; crown brown; eyes dark brown; face entirely brown; head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin obtusely rounded; crown short, broad, slightly narrower than width of eyes, produced anteriorly about ¼ of entire length, lateral margins convergent basally; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum large, about half longer medially than crown, surface bullated, mesonotum large, about 1/3 longer medially than pronotum; clypeus long, broad, lateral margins broadly convex; clypellus short, about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, longitudinally inflated medially, apex flared laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[192,1441,867,1403]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,448,1219,1243]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view with long robust caudodorsal process, apex aviform, glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[280,385,1251,1275]" captionStart="Figures 141-147" captionStartId="152.[192,287,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[275,1334,212,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-18@152.[263,1348,192,1701]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figures 141-147. Genitalia, Hiatusorus aviformis, sp. nov. 141) Male pygofer, lateral view. 142) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view. 143) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view. 144) Style, lateral view. 145) Style, dorsal view. 146) Connective, caudal view. 147) Subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181630/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 141</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, tubular, shaft slightly inflated in distal 1/5, in lateral view sinuate, narrow incurvation in apical 1/5, apex toothed, gonopore subapical (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1160,1283,1307]" captionStart="Figures 141-147" captionStartId="152.[192,287,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[275,1334,212,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-18@152.[263,1348,192,1701]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figures 141-147. Genitalia, Hiatusorus aviformis, sp. nov. 141) Male pygofer, lateral view. 142) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view. 143) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view. 144) Style, lateral view. 145) Style, dorsal view. 146) Connective, caudal view. 147) Subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181630/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 142, 143</figureCitation>
); style with moderately long apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[388,550,1315,1339]" captionStart="Figures 141-147" captionStartId="152.[192,287,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[275,1334,212,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-18@152.[263,1348,192,1701]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figures 141-147. Genitalia, Hiatusorus aviformis, sp. nov. 141) Male pygofer, lateral view. 142) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view. 143) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view. 144) Style, lateral view. 145) Style, dorsal view. 146) Connective, caudal view. 147) Subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181630/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 144, 145</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective short, narrow (
<figureCitation box="[976,1137,1315,1339]" captionStart="Figures 141-147" captionStartId="152.[192,287,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[275,1334,212,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-18@152.[263,1348,192,1701]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figures 141-147. Genitalia, Hiatusorus aviformis, sp. nov. 141) Male pygofer, lateral view. 142) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view. 143) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view. 144) Style, lateral view. 145) Style, dorsal view. 146) Connective, caudal view. 147) Subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181630/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 142, 143</figureCitation>
); connective small, anterior arms curved apically, medial ridge incomplete, stem small, subrectangulate (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1290,1347,1371]" captionStart="Figures 141-147" captionStartId="152.[192,287,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[275,1334,212,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-18@152.[263,1348,192,1701]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figures 141-147. Genitalia, Hiatusorus aviformis, sp. nov. 141) Male pygofer, lateral view. 142) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view. 143) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view. 144) Style, lateral view. 145) Style, dorsal view. 146) Connective, caudal view. 147) Subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181630/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 146</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate long, broad, with moderately long, slender apical spine, sparsely setose apically (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1341,1379,1403]" captionStart="Figures 141-147" captionStartId="152.[192,287,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[275,1334,212,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-18@152.[263,1348,192,1701]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figures 141-147. Genitalia, Hiatusorus aviformis, sp. nov. 141) Male pygofer, lateral view. 142) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view. 143) Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view. 144) Style, lateral view. 145) Style, dorsal view. 146) Connective, caudal view. 147) Subgenital plate, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181630/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 147</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
